            "body": "also for following code\n\n```\nclass A\n{\n    public:\n        A(int, int, int);\n    private:\n        int a;\n        int b;\n        int c;\n    private:\n        int d;\n};\n\n// wanted\nA::A(int aa, int bb, int cc)\n    : a(aa)\n    , b(bb)\n    , c(cc)\n{\n    d = 0;\n}\n\n// gg=G gives by vim/gvim/nvim\n// update:\n// this wrong indent is caused by indent_c.c:cin_isfuncdecl()\n// vim incorrectly recognize : a(aa) as a function decl.\n// \n    A::A(int aa, int bb, int cc)\n    : a(aa)\n    , b(bb)\n      , c(cc)\n{\n    d = 0;\n}\n```\n",
